%% Diagram: TanStack Query cache lifecycle (staleTime vs gcTime)
%% Type: state diagram
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Fresh: useQuery mounts
    Fresh --> Stale: staleTime elapses
    Stale --> Fresh: refetch returns
    Fresh --> InactiveCached: last observer unmounts
    Stale --> InactiveCached: last observer unmounts
    InactiveCached --> Fresh: new observer + refetch ok
    InactiveCached --> Stale: new observer (still stale)
    InactiveCached --> [*]: gcTime elapses (collected)

    note right of Fresh
        Default staleTime is 0.
        No background refetch is
        triggered while data is fresh.
    end note

    note right of Stale
        Refetch on mount, window focus,
        reconnect, or explicit invalidate.
    end note

    note right of InactiveCached
        Default gcTime is 5 minutes.
        Inactive means no observers.
        Re-mount within gcTime keeps data.
    end note
